---
const credentials = [
  'Brandeis (Heller School) & CMU — three graduate degrees',
  'PM Youth Excellence Award (2022) · ADB Climate Resilience Award (2024)',
  'Featured in Internet Society\'s global documentary on digital inequality',
  'Only Pakistani organisation selected for AI Opportunity Fund: Asia-Pacific',
  'Atlas Corps, British Council & DO School Fellow',
  'Funded by AVPN, Google.org, Internet Society & Asian Development Bank',
];
---

<section class="story section" id="story">
  <div class="story__inner container">
    <div class="story__left">
      <div class="story__left-sticky">
        <span class="eyebrow reveal">Story</span>
        <h2 class="story__heading reveal">
          The mission came first.<br />
          <em>The tech followed.</em>
        </h2>
        <ul class="story__credentials reveal">
          {credentials.map((item) => (
            <li class="story__credential">
              <span class="story__credential-mark" aria-hidden="true">&#9670;</span>
              {item}
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="story__right">
      <div class="story__narrative">
        <p class="story__paragraph story__paragraph--dropcap reveal">
          I came to AI through development work — not the other way around. After years studying how communities are shaped by systems of power and exclusion, I watched artificial intelligence become the most consequential of those systems. The question underneath all of my work has always been the same: who gets left out?
        </p>

        <p class="story__paragraph reveal">
          Urdu AI started from that gap — and grew into Pakistan&rsquo;s leading AI literacy platform, now reaching over one million people through social media, a weekly newsletter, a mobile app, and workshops across the country. The largest Urdu-language AI education community in the world, built without a venture round and without corporate backing.
        </p>

        <blockquote class="story__pullquote reveal">
          <p>220 million people speak Urdu. Almost none of the world&rsquo;s AI education reaches them. So I built the infrastructure to change that.</p>
        </blockquote>

        <p class="story__paragraph reveal">
          Then came PakSpeed — because you cannot talk about digital inclusion without honest data on who actually has connectivity and who doesn&rsquo;t. In its first seven days, Pakistan&rsquo;s first community-owned internet speed monitoring network logged over 15,000 tests. Real data. Real accountability. Built for the people it measures.
        </p>

        <p class="story__paragraph reveal">
          WANG and its innovation lab WALI have been working on the ground for over a decade — girls&rsquo; education, flood rehabilitation, rural digital literacy, and youth leadership in communities where the digital divide is not a statistic but a daily reality. After the 2022 floods, WANG built fifty sustainable homes for women-led families in Balochistan. Trusted and funded by Internet Society, AVPN, Google.org, and the Asian Development Bank.
        </p>

        <p class="story__paragraph reveal">
          AI for Edu brings AI integration to Canadian K-12 and post-secondary classrooms. AI Viewer breaks down the global AI landscape for a professional English-language audience. PakSpeed holds ISPs accountable with real connectivity data. Five platforms, two continents, thirty-five million people reached every month.
        </p>

        <div class="story__documentary reveal">
          <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F0aSyRMBrLE" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="story__documentary-link">
            <span class="story__documentary-badge">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polygon points="5 3 19 12 5 21 5 3"></polygon></svg>
            </span>
            <span class="story__documentary-text">
              <span class="story__documentary-label">Featured Documentary</span>
              <span class="story__documentary-title">Tackling Inequality Using the Internet — Internet Society (2023)</span>
            </span>
            <svg class="story__documentary-arrow" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M4 12l8-8M5 4h7v7" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </a>
        </div>

        <p class="story__paragraph story__paragraph--closing reveal">
          Different platforms. Different communities. One conviction: AI should belong to everyone who needs it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .story {
    background: var(--cream);
  }

  .story__inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 35% 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
  }

  .story__left-sticky {
    position: sticky;
    top: 6rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.75rem;
  }

  .story__heading em {
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .story__credentials {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .story__credential {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .story__credential-mark {
    color: var(--gold);
    font-size: 0.5rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }

  .story__narrative {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .story__paragraph {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.92;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .story__paragraph--dropcap::first-letter {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 3.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    float: left;
    line-height: 0.8;
    margin-right: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.15rem;
    color: var(--rust);
  }

  .story__paragraph--closing {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .story__pullquote {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
    background: rgba(184, 145, 60, 0.06);
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius) var(--radius) 0;
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .story__pullquote p {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.55;
    max-width: none;
  }

  /* Documentary link */
  .story__documentary {
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .story__documentary-link {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: rgba(184, 145, 60, 0.06);
    border: 1px solid rgba(184, 145, 60, 0.15);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    transition: border-color 0.3s ease, background 0.3s ease, gap 0.3s ease;
  }

  .story__documentary-link:hover {
    border-color: rgba(184, 145, 60, 0.35);
    background: rgba(184, 145, 60, 0.1);
  }

  .story__documentary-badge {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--rust);
    color: #fff;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }

  .story__documentary-link:hover .story__documentary-badge {
    transform: scale(1.08);
  }

  .story__documentary-text {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.15rem;
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .story__documentary-label {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  .story__documentary-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .story__documentary-arrow {
    color: var(--rust);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }

  .story__documentary-link:hover .story__documentary-arrow {
    transform: translate(2px, -2px);
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .story__inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 3rem;
    }

    .story__left-sticky {
      position: static;
    }
  }
</style>
